  "title" : "How to use a Java 8 lambda to sort a Stream in reverse order?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm using a Java lambda to sort a list.</p>\n<p>How can I sort it in a reverse way?</p>\n<p>I saw <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5894818/how-to-sort-arraylistlong-in-decreasing-order\">How to sort ArrayList&lt;Long&gt; in decreasing order?</a>, but I want to use a Java 8 lambda.</p>\n<p>Here is my code (I used * -1) as a hack:</p>\n<pre><code>Arrays.asList(files).stream()\n    .filter(file -&gt; isNameLikeBaseLine(file, baseLineFile.getName()))\n    .sorted(new Comparator&lt;File&gt;() {\n        public int compare(File o1, File o2) {\n            int answer;\n            if (o1.lastModified() == o2.lastModified()) {\n                answer = 0;\n            } else if (o1.lastModified() &gt; o2.lastModified()) {\n                answer = 1;\n            } else {\n                answer = -1;\n            }\n            return -1 * answer;\n        }\n    })\n    .skip(numOfNewestToLeave)\n    .forEach(item -&gt; item.delete());\n</code></pre>\n"
